Baby hammerhead sharks are born in groups
of 12 to 15 and as soon as they're born they're

00:00:06.549 --> 00:00:08.500
orphaned by their parents.

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:12.730
The litter huddles together and swims toward
warmer water until they are big enough to

00:00:12.730 --> 00:00:14.850
